definitions.definition: To take a view of the contents of; search in, either with the eyes or by hand.
definitions.example: Airport security looked through her purse and confiscated her nail scissors.

definitions.definition: To penetrate with the understanding; to see through.
(often with "right") To appear or pretend not to see something or someone who is clearly visible.
definitions.example: I tried to get Michele's attention at the party, but she looked right through me!
